title.rendered: Quetta vs Lahore, Pakistan T20 League 2023: Pitch Report, Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Pitch Report for National Stadium, Karachi

Venue: National Stadium, Karachi

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 169

2nd innings average score: 151

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Team for Quetta vs Lahore

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs

Rashid Khan has joined the Lahore squad after finishing his national duty.

Quetta: Jason Roy, Martin Guptill, Sarfaraz Ahmed (c & wk), Mohammad Nawaz, Iftikhar Ahmed, Odean Smith, Abdul Bangalzai, Mohammad Hafeez, Naseem Shah, Mohammad Hasnain, Qais Ahmad

Lahore: Fakhar Zaman, Mirza Tahir Baig, Shai Hope (wk), Kamran Ghulam, Hussain Talat, Sikandar Raza, David Wiese/Rashid Khan, Liam Dawson, Shaheen Afridi (c), Haris Rauf, Zaman Khan

Also Read:

Multan vs Karachi, Pakistan T20 League 2023: Fantasy Tips

UAE vs Namibia, CWC League 2019-23: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Sarfaraz Ahmed has scored 303 runs at 33.7 against Lahore. He has also earned useful points for seven dismissals.

Mohammad Nawaz has used his dual skills to good effect against Lahore. He averages 23.9 with the bat and has taken 10 wickets including the best figures of 2 for 4.

Fakhar Zaman enjoys batting against Quetta – 410 runs at 37.3 in 12 innings. He has generated the 50-point bonus in three of the last four such matches.

Haris Rauf has troubled Quetta batters in the past, picking up nine wickets in six matches.

Shaheen Afridi and Rashid Khan have featured in the Best11 in each of the last five matches.

Iftikhar Ahmed has smashed a century and four fifties in 14 T20s in 2023 to aggregate 433 runs at 54. To add to that, he can also earn points with the ball.

Zaman Khan has gone wicketless in only one of the last 14 T20s, and thus features in the Best11 in four of the last five matches.

Jason Roy’s recent numbers – 141 runs in his last eight T20s – are a bit disappointing,  but the fact that he scored a century against Lahore last year must boost his confidence.

In the last three games at Karachi, the seamers have picked 67% of the wickets.
